# edit.m8script — enter a note at phrase 00 row 0, confirm it lands
# Key sequence from save_reload.m8script (proven to set note to C-4)
# Starting state: SONG screen, phrase 00, row 0, column 0 (note column)
# Note starts empty (0xFF). X on an empty note cell inserts a default C-4
# (UiEditHelpers.h InsertDefault, fired on X's own down event -- NOT via
# editHeld+UP, which is a separate mechanism for Instrument-screen fields;
# see M8_APP_AUTOMATION_SPEC.md Tier 4 notes).
#
# Explicit `load` added 2026-07-17: this script previously had none, relying
# on the ambient boot song (songs/sunrise.m8s). Since sunrise.m8s already has
# C-4 at phrase 00 row 0, the assertion below passed regardless of whether
# the edit sequence did anything at all -- confirmed by tracing dump_screen
# after each keypress, which showed "C-4" present *before* any key was
# pressed. V4EMPTY.m8s (used here, and by save_reload.m8script) genuinely has
# no note there, so this now actually exercises the insert path.

load third_party/m8-files-cxx/examples/songs/V4EMPTY.m8s
wait 1
assert_no_error

# Navigate to PHRASE screen: SONG -> CHAIN -> PHRASE
key SHIFT+RIGHT
key SHIFT+RIGHT
wait 1

# Enter edit mode (X), press UP to set note to C-4, exit edit mode (X)
key X
key UP
key X
wait 1

# Verify the note is visible
assert_screen row 3 contains "C-4"
